      "content": "When the pattern feels so absolute, it can feel like the loop *is* your reality, which is terrifying. But even the most entrenched patterns are ultimately comprised of individual actions, however small they seem. Instead of aiming for a grand overhaul, maybe you could look closely at the moments *just before* the crash. Understanding the trigger might reveal a tiny point of leverage within the loop.",
      "source": "target",
