      "content": "That feeling of being trapped in a rigged system is profoundly heavy, and the urge to just stop is a natural response to that intense pressure. If the entire structure feels inescapable, then sometimes the most powerful act is to simply step out of the arena entirely. Allowing yourself to cease the relentless effort, even for a short time, might be the only true pause you can grant yourself right now.",
